analysis: The documents primarily concern land reservations, withdrawals, modifications, and revocations in Alaska. These actions are taken for various purposes, including military use, road construction, agriculture, and other governmental activities. Many of the documents cite the authority of the acts of June 25, 1910, and August 24, 1912. The documents also describe specific locations using metes and bounds or references to existing surveys and landmarks.
title: Alaskan Land Management Directives
